# v0.62 — Pause Menu

### New Files
- `scripts/pause_menu.gd` — Runtime pause overlay
  - Full-screen overlay with semi-transparent backdrop
  - Resume, Restart Chapter, Mute/Unmute, Quit to Title buttons
  - Blocks input behind it (mouse_filter = STOP)
  - ESC key toggles pause; R restarts (pauses first), C toggles chapter manager
  - `Engine.time_scale = 0` when paused, z_index=100
  - Works in both native and HTML5 builds

### Updated
- `scripts/level_manager.gd` — instantiates pause_menu via script.new(), calls setup()
  - _input() checks pause_menu state before scene reload / chapter manager toggle
- `project.godot` — added `pause` input action (ESC key, keycode 4194305)
- `scenes/main.tscn` — instructions label updated: added ESC=Pause text
- `scenes/title_screen.tscn` — version bumped to v0.62

### Design Rationale
- Runtime UI = no .tscn fragility, works the same across scenes
- Pause stops combat, dialogue, and all timers
- Mute button syncs with AudioManager state
- Quit to Title clears GameState chapter data and returns to title screen

