# v0.63 — Dodge Roll + Screen Fade Transitions

### New Files
- `scripts/screen_fader.gd` — Autoload CanvasLayer with ColorRect overlay
  - `fade_to_black(duration)` returns Signal → tween to Color.BLACK
  - `fade_from_black(duration)` returns Signal → tween to Color.TRANSPARENT
  - `flash_white(duration)` returns Signal → brief white flash
- `scenes/screen_fader.tscn` — CanvasLayer (layer=99) + full-screen ColorRect (mouse_filter=PASS)

### Updated
- `project.godot`
  - Added `skill1` input action (LEFT SHIFT, keycode 4194325)
  - Added `ScreenFader` to `[autoload]`
- `scripts/player.gd`
  - Dodge roll: `is_dodging` state, I-frames during roll (no damage)
  - Constants: `DODGE_DURATION=0.25s`, `DODGE_COOLDOWN=1.2s`, `DODGE_SPEED_MULT=3.0`
  - Dash in facing direction at 3× speed during roll
  - Visual: modulate opacity to 50%, flash back to white on end
  - Attack hitbox disabled during dodge; no attacking while dodging
  - `skill1` input wired → `_start_dodge()`; mobile `skill1_btn` now functional
- `scripts/level_manager.gd`
  - `_finish_chapter_complete()` now fades to black, increments chapter, reloads scene
  - `_ready()` fades from black on level load
  - Updated control hint: added LEFT SHIFT = dodge
- `scripts/autoload/audio_manager.gd`
  - Added `dodge_roll` to SFX preload list (placeholder, no asset yet)

### Design Rationale
- Dodge roll: gives player a defensive option without adding shield/block complexity
  - I-frames prevent "tank everything" — requires timing, not mashing
  - Short duration (0.25s) + long cooldown (1.2s) = high risk/reward
  - Visual opacity communicates invulnerability window
- Fade transitions: polish for chapter flow
  - Eliminates jarring instant reload on chapter complete
  - Consistent with pause menu overlay pattern (CanvasLayer autoload)
  - Can be reused for death respawn, cutscene transitions

### Version Changes
- PROMPT_PACK.md updated: skill system marked functional, UI note updated

### Zero Parse Errors ✅ (manual review + GDScript syntax)
### Commit: `67a8111`

