# v0.67 — AnimatedSprite2D + Procedural Sprite Sheets

### New Files
- `scripts/generate_sprites_v2.py` — Procedural sprite sheet generator
  - Generates horizontal strip sprite sheets (idle/walk/attack) for all characters
  - Player: 3 idle, 3 walk, 4 attack frames
  - Skeleton: 2 idle, 2 walk, 2 attack frames
  - Captain: 2 idle, 2 walk, 2 attack frames (with shield overlay)
  - Archer: 2 idle, 2 walk frames
  - Merchant: 2 idle frames
- `assets/art/characters/player_idle.png` (3 frames, 96×32px)
- `assets/art/characters/player_walk.png` (3 frames, 96×32px)
- `assets/art/characters/player_attack.png` (4 frames, 128×32px)
- `assets/art/enemies/skeleton_idle.png` (2 frames, 64×32px)
- `assets/art/enemies/skeleton_walk.png` (2 frames, 64×32px)
- `assets/art/enemies/skeleton_attack.png` (2 frames, 64×32px)
- `assets/art/enemies/captain_idle.png` (2 frames, 64×32px)
- `assets/art/enemies/captain_walk.png` (2 frames, 64×32px)
- `assets/art/enemies/captain_attack.png` (2 frames, 64×32px)
- `assets/art/enemies/archer_idle.png` (2 frames, 64×32px)
- `assets/art/enemies/archer_walk.png` (2 frames, 64×32px)
- `assets/art/npcs/merchant_idle.png` (2 frames, 64×32px)

### Updated Scenes
- `scenes/player.tscn` — Polygon2D → AnimatedSprite2D with SpriteFrames (idle/walk/attack)
- `scenes/skeleton.tscn` — Polygon2D → AnimatedSprite2D with SpriteFrames (idle/walk/attack)
- `scenes/skeleton_captain.tscn` — Polygon2D → AnimatedSprite2D + Shield overlay preserved
- `scenes/skeleton_archer.tscn` — Polygon2D → AnimatedSprite2D (idle/walk)
- `scenes/merchant_ally.tscn` — Polygon2D → AnimatedSprite2D (idle)

### Updated Scripts
- `scripts/player.gd` — `$Polygon2D` → `$AnimatedSprite2D`, play("idle/walk/attack") state machine
- `scripts/skeleton.gd` — `$Polygon2D` → `$AnimatedSprite2D`, animation state machine (idle/chase/attack)
- `scripts/skeleton_captain.gd` — `$Polygon2D` → `$AnimatedSprite2D`, animation state machine + shield overlay
- `scripts/skeleton_archer.gd` — `$Polygon2D` → `$AnimatedSprite2D`, animation state machine (idle/walk/move)

### Architecture
- All characters now use AnimatedSprite2D with named animations
- Animation states: idle, walk, attack (per character type)
- Player: idle↔walk on movement, attack on input, dodge uses modulate opacity
- Enemies: idle when stationary, walk when chasing, attack on attack
- Captain retains Shield Polygon2D overlay (visual only, separate from sprite)
- Procedural sprites: 16×16 logical px, scaled 2× = 32×32 display, palette-based pixel art
- `generate_sprites_v2.py` can be re-run to regenerate all sprite sheets

### Must-Have #1 Status: ✅ DONE (v0.67)
Procedural sprites + AnimatedSprite2D replaces all Polygon2D visuals.
Polygon2D kept only as captain shield overlay (visual effect, not character body).

### Zero Parse Errors ✅ (manual review)
